			<div class="article-correspondence layout-item fill-pattern-light">
		<div class="layout-item-intro">
			<h2>Correspondence</h2>
			<a class="xsmall link-alt" href="https://www.thesunmagazine.org/letter-to-the-editor">Write a Letter to the Editor&nbsp;&#9656;</a>
		</div>

		<div id="article-correspondences" class="correspondences correspondences-collapsed">
								<div class="block-correspondence" id="2770">
		<blockquote class="quote-2">
			<p>I was moved to tears by Sharman Apt Russell&rsquo;s &ldquo;<a href="/article/1721">Feast and Famine</a>&rdquo; [March 1996]. I was also disappointed by her reductionist dismissal of key aspects of the hunger problem; overpopulation and environmental degradation, she says, are &ldquo;not the problem.&nbsp;.&nbsp;.&nbsp;. The problem is a lack of human will.&rdquo;</p>

<p>It seems to me that, as we generate the requisite human will, we are forced to come to terms with these real aspects of the problem &mdash; as well as with the implications of our own dietary choices. The article begins with Russell eating a hamburger. Anyone familiar with John Robbins&rsquo;s <em>Diet for a New America </em>can see the contradiction here.</p>

<p>To the extent that we stop consuming the products of animal agriculture, we not only make a dent in the problem of world hunger but also reduce our complicity in another form of massive suffering &mdash; the use and abuse of highly sentient animals in the production of meat, eggs, and dairy products. And we ourselves become healthier.</p>

<p>It&rsquo;s nice to know that, at least in this case, what&rsquo;s best for us is also best for all the animals and humans of the world.</p>
							<p class="quote-2-author">Billy Ray Boyd<br>San Francisco, California</p>
					</blockquote>
	</div>

								<div class="block-correspondence-respond fill-pattern-light" id="2771">
								<p><a href="/contributors/sharman-apt-russell"><strong>Sharman Apt Russell</strong></a> responds:</p>
							<p>I agree completely with Billy Ray Boyd. My essay on famine is part of a larger collection in which I discuss animal rights and animal agriculture. I also very much hope that Boyd is right; that we are generating the requisite human will.</p>
	</div>


					</div>

				<div class="text-center">
			<button class="b b-1 xsmall js-b-readmore-correspondence" data-collapsible="#article-correspondences" data-label="Read More Letters">Read More Letters</button>
